        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 6:32PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 632 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles southwest of Brownsville, or 8 miles south of Lead, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sturgis, Galena, Tilford, Brownsville, Fort Meade, Apple Springs, and
Roubaix Lake.

This includes Interstate 90 in South Dakota between Mile Markers 27
and 41.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
